Enum Constant Detail

UNAUTHORIZED_REQUEST

public static final ProtocolException.Error UNAUTHORIZED_REQUEST
Used when responding to a request that do not have access token. No Error code or explanation must be returned.

INVALID_TOKEN

public static final ProtocolException.Error INVALID_TOKEN
The access token provided is invalid. Used when receiving an expired token which cannot be refreshed to indicate to the client that a new authorization is necessary.

EXPIRED_TOKEN

public static final ProtocolException.Error EXPIRED_TOKEN
The access token provided has expired. Used only this error code when the client is expected to be able to handle the response and request a new access token using the refresh token issued with the expired access token.

INVALID_REQUEST

public static final ProtocolException.Error INVALID_REQUEST
The request is missing a required parameter, includes an unknown parameter or parameter value, repeats a parameter, includes multiple credentials, utilizes more than one mechanism for authenticating the client, or is otherwise malformed.

UNSUPPORTED_GRANT_TYPE

public static final ProtocolException.Error UNSUPPORTED_GRANT_TYPE
The access grant included - its type or another attribute - is not supported by the authorization server.

INVALID_CLIENT

public static final ProtocolException.Error INVALID_CLIENT
The client identifier provided is invalid, the client failed to authenticate, or the client provided multiple client credentials.

INVALID_SCOPE
